*  GECS COST OF GOODS SOLD AMOUNTED TO $8.5 BILLION IN 2000, COMPARED WITH $8.0

BILLION IN 1999 AND $6.8 BILLION IN 1998, AND RELATES TO IT SOLUTIONS AND

WARDS. THE INCREASE IN 2000 AND 1999 PRIMARILY REFLECTS THE CONSOLIDATION OF

