LOSSES, INCLUDED $6,323 MILLION AND $5,832 MILLION, RESPECTIVELY, FROM SALES OF

GOODS AND SERVICES TO CUSTOMERS, AND $233 MILLION AND $296 MILLION,

RESPECTIVELY, FROM TRANSACTIONS WITH ASSOCIATED COMPANIES.

CURRENT RECEIVABLES OF $227 MILLION AT YEAR-END 2000 AND

$203 MILLION AT YEAR-END 1999 AROSE FROM SALES, PRINCIPALLY OF AIRCRAFT ENGINE

GOODS AND SERVICES, ON OPEN ACCOUNT TO VARIOUS AGENCIES OF THE U.S. GOVERNMENT,

WHICH IS GE'S LARGEST SINGLE CUSTOMER. ABOUT 3%, 4% AND 4% OF GE'S SALES OF

GOODS AND SERVICES WERE TO THE U.S. GOVERNMENT IN 2000, 1999 AND 1998,

RESPECTIVELY.

