=================================================================================================================

FOR GE, GROSS PROFIT FROM SALES IS SALES OF GOODS AND SERVICES LESS COSTS OF

GOODS AND SERVICES SOLD. FOR GECS, OPERATING PROFIT IS "EARNINGS BEFORE INCOME

TAXES."

EARNINGS-PER-SHARE AMOUNTS FOR EACH QUARTER ARE REQUIRED

TO BE COMPUTED INDEPENDENTLY. AS A RESULT, THEIR SUM DOES NOT EQUAL THE TOTAL

YEAR EARNINGS-PER-SHARE AMOUNTS FOR DILUTED EARNINGS PER SHARE IN 2000 AND 1999,

AND FOR BASIC EARNINGS PER SHARE IN 2000. PER-SHARE AMOUNTS HAVE BEEN ADJUSTED

FOR THE 3-FOR-1 STOCK SPLIT EFFECTIVE ON APRIL 27, 2000.

